{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a814ae79-5550-406b-a684-6a1d677e2ed7","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove this line entirely -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n   MSTest.Sdk 3.8+ defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is not set.\n\n2. **Update your test runner command** — use `dotnet test` as before, but note that CLI output format may differ slightly.\n\n3. **If you use `.runsettings`**, most settings carry over, but review the [Microsoft.Testing.Platform docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform) for any incompatibilities.\n\n4. **If you reference `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`**, you can remove it — MSTest.Sdk already handles the platform dependency.\n\nThat's it — the SDK handles the rest. Rebuild and run `dotnet test` to verify.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6d27b731-66ab-4eda-b115-f0ef05dcad14","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project that uses MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0. This is a knowledge question, not a code change request. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":330},"id":"8910e369-c5c8-49cd-96e6-eddbc1a3b289","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:04:36.931Z","parentId":"85472463-4f9f-48dd-ab90-9c0adf7ce3e1"}
